name: Siobak Babi Khe Lok
address: Jl. Surapati No.66, Kp. Baru, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia
review 1: One of the oldest standing Siobak Singaraja until these days. A portion of siobak contains meats, ear, inner parts and pork rind crackers, but you can choose to combine them all or just choose specific part (like meat only) since some people don't eat organs. The taste was authentic and can only be found at some parts of Bali only.
review 2: Good food in Singaraja! Siobak Babi Khe Lok is a delicious dish that is worth trying if you have the opportunity to do so in Singaraja. Make sure to come and visit! Cheap and very very good!
review 3: Part of the northern Bali culinary that you should not miss. The og outlet has been in operation since 1960s. The siobak (sao rou, roast pork) which was originally a Chinese cuisine was introduced by immigrants and then assimilated and transformed into their own version. The dark sauce used is rather spicy and various cuts (innards, lean meat, belly)  are up for you to choose. Fried skin was also provided as part of the meal. I tried the mixed one as it provides layers of textures and flavors but found it very ordinary. Service was fast and the price was fair.
review 4:
The infamous siobak babi in Singaraja. So packed with people, mostly Chinese Indo-a great indicator of a tasty food- and I was not wrong. It's overall tasty. Too bad I'm not into the sauce they used here.

Spent 85k for 2 person.

name: X-ecutive Karaoke
address: V3WW+JJR, Kampung Baru, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81114, Indonesia
review 1: The most affordable family karaoke in the city. Helpful staff, clean, rather complete choice of songs available considering it is very affordable. Every room has a security camera and that's very good. One thing I don't like is that I can hear other people singing when I checked in  because the rooms are not totally soundproof. This means other people can also hear my voice when they checked in and I'm not comfortable knowing that. But still, I will definitely return because of the price.
review 2: One stop music entertainment, karaoke, music recording, event organizer.

name: Loving Hut - Singaraja
address: Jl. Surapati No.43, Kp. Baru, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81113, Indonesia
review 1:
Cheap, delicious and perfect for vegans to try out the traditional Balinese dishes! Loved the nut satay ‚ù§ Especially because it doesn't taste too much like that typical mock meat flavour but more veggie-like.
The fruit juices are not recommendable tho. They are cheap as well but way too watery, I could've skipped on those. Unfortunately they don't serve dessert. The only thing that is really striking me a lot is when I told them I don't want a straw for my juice and I still get it...
review 2:
Staff was mostly away in incognito mode than on standby mode, well i guess that's why there is a bell near thw cashier table üòÇ

Many option, good taste, small portion, affirac will only turn on when guest arrives.
review 3: The food here is amazing.  I had the vegan mock meat teriyaki, satay skewers and mushroom rice. The price is also very cheap compared to other vegan restaurants in Bali aimed at tourists. I would highly recommend this.
review 4: It's written vegan & vegetarian food, but menu has some confusing options. We ordered veg burger, french fries, veg. Pizza & ice tea. Taste was okay, doable, but quantity of fries & pizza was less compared to rate. According to the service & food, place seems little overpriced, but can't complain in a foreign land. Happy to find a Veg. Restaurant close by our stay at Singaraja, Bali. :)
review 5: I love all the dishes they do, especially the fried rice with mushroom and vegan satay. The most affordable, the cleanest and the tastiest vegan restaurant in Singaraja. Even though you're not vegan, I can guarantee that you will enjoy the dishes. You will be surprised that there is no animal products in any of the dishes. I visit at least once a month now. Very recommended!

review 1: In Bali, there are several pork food type that are served. I could say that this is the best pork food type A and for the type B the winner is at another place. review 2: Definitely a must visit when I go to Singaraja, legendary meals. Come early to get everything complete, the crisp and samsam skewers are the best

name: Sate Tauco Kho Lin
address: Jl. P. Plores, Kp. Baru, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81113, Indonesia
review 1:
Yumm yummm yummm‚Ä¶ I tried their satay tauco, and for me who doesn‚Äôt eat big for breakfast it is such a perfect portion. It is sweet, so if u‚Äôre not into sweet seasoning you can try other type of satay. They also server other complementary food.

If you are one to enjoy the food and story of the place, well this place owner is a Chinese peranakan person, and his balinese wife. Koh Lin‚Äôs family have been selling satay for 3 generations. It started with his grandpa who used to sell satay on a shoulder pole in front of an old theater. After it was demolished, his dad moved and rented the warung where it stands today. The warung is a walking distance to a temple just behind the housing are. So it is a perfect stop before a little walking tour
review 2: Singaraja's best pork satay combo with soup.
review 3: Tasty and delicious tauco satay and Semur soup
